This extends from [TEAMCAL-537|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/TEAMCAL-537]

Please see this feedback from a customer:

{quote}It does seem odd, and going to extremes, that first any user could change a calendar to any name in their own profile, then nobody but the create user can change the calendar name.

Consider the use case - user creates calendar and leaves the organisation. Then nobody can change the calendar name unless administrators reset the user's password and modify calendar name that way, or directly modify the 'owner' in the database. Both seem a little cumbersome. It would be useful if confluence-administrators could modify calendar names regardless of who owns them.{quote}

