OnDemand currently has a test for Team Calendars testing the JIRA integration and other functionality. This test is causing us to waste a lot of time in the moment since Team Calendars changes the DOM of its UI on a regular basis, and due to the separate repositories it is hard to fix a test ahead of a release.

We just had the case where Matt fixed the test to work for TC 2.4.1, but the 5.0-OD-4 release contains TC 2.3.0. Thus his fix worked for our [CBAC build|https://confluence-bamboo.atlassian.com/browse/COD-MODAT-1601], which takes the confluence-production-integration branch from the ondemand-fireball repository and bakes that together with a snapshot from the Confluence master branch. In the same time, that broke the [BEAC build|https://bamboo.extranet.atlassian.com/browse/JST-JSTGIT21-1] which runs against a released version of Confluence in order to prepare integration into OnDemand. Having to maintain a separate branch where this fixes can be applied against a snapshot of Confluence would be too much effort imo, as the person releasing would have to know which commits to merge in. Instead, we should write the above mentioned test in a backwards-compatible manner, that is to reuse the page objects of TC. If that is not possible the spec of that test should be extracted and re-written in TC.

