{calendar:id=1850f164-3756-4405-b1d0-ae53f8d2572c|defaultView=month} 

However it would be ideal for us if we could request a JIRA project name in the calendar macro for example:

{calendar:type=jira|project=PROJABC|showversions=yes|showissues=yes|title=Project ABC|defaultView=month} 

The reason for this request is we have a set of pages in Confluence for each of our Jira projects (which we have a lot of), and we use user macros to simplify the management of these pages. e.g. we use a custom macro like {displayproject:id=PROJABC} which goes away and picks up all the relevant information from Jira for that project, and we would like to include the calendar in this without having to add and identify the calendar id for each project.

